SIMPLE: perturbation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Perturbation
<hw>Per`tur*ba"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>perturbatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>perturbation</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of perturbing, or the state of being perturbed;
esp., agitation of mind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>A disturbance in the regular
elliptic or other motion of a heavenly body, produced by some force
additional to that which causes its regular motion; <as>as, the
<ex>perturbations</ex> of the planets are caused by their attraction on
each other</as>.</def> <rj><au>Newcomb.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perturbational</ent>⟦br⟧
